<!-- Jinja2 structural template — uses {{ variable }} placeholders. Read as a structural reference; no rendering pipeline needed. -->
---
title: "{{ title }}"
artifact: SPEC-{{ number }}
track: implementable
status: {{ status | default("Proposed") }}
author: {{ author }}
created: {{ created_date }}
last-updated: {{ last_updated_date }}
priority-weight: ""  # optional: high | medium | low. Omit to inherit from parent Epic or Initiative.
type: {{ type | default("") }}
parent-epic: {{ parent_epic | default("") }}
parent-initiative: {{ parent_initiative | default("") }}
linked-artifacts:
{%- for artifact in linked_artifacts | default([]) %}
  - {{ artifact }}
{%- endfor %}
depends-on-artifacts:
{%- for dep in depends_on_artifacts | default([]) %}
  - {{ dep }}
{%- endfor %}
addresses:
{%- for pp in addresses | default([]) %}
  - {{ pp }}
{%- endfor %}
evidence-pool: {{ evidence_pool | default("") }}
source-issue: {{ source_issue | default("") }}
swain-do: required
---

# {{ title }}

## Problem Statement

{{ problem_statement | default("What problem this spec addresses — scoped from the parent Epic's goal.") }}

## Desired Outcomes

{{ desired_outcomes | default("How does shipping this spec make our personas better off? Who benefits and what changes for them? Connect to the parent epic/initiative's aspirations, or articulate the aspiration directly for standalone specs.") }}

## External Behavior

{{ external_behavior | default("Inputs, outputs, preconditions, postconditions, constraints, and interfaces.") }}

## Acceptance Criteria

{{ acceptance_criteria | default("Given/When/Then scenarios — concise and verifiable.") }}

{%- if type == "bug" %}

## Reproduction Steps

{{ reproduction_steps | default("Steps to reproduce the defect.") }}

## Severity

{{ severity | default("critical | high | medium | low") }}

## Expected vs. Actual Behavior

**Expected:** {{ expected_behavior | default("What should happen.") }}

**Actual:** {{ actual_behavior | default("What happens instead.") }}
{%- endif %}

## Verification

<!-- Populated when entering Testing phase. Maps each acceptance criterion
     to its evidence: test name, manual check, or demo scenario.
     Leave empty until Testing. -->

| Criterion | Evidence | Result |
|-----------|----------|--------|
{%- for criterion in verification | default([]) %}
| {{ criterion.name }} | {{ criterion.evidence }} | {{ criterion.result }} |
{%- endfor %}

## Scope & Constraints

{{ scope_constraints | default("Boundaries, non-goals, and token-budget awareness.") }}

{#- When superpowers is detected, omit this section entirely.
    SPECs become thin contracts — the execution plan is generated
    by superpowers' writing-plans skill at implementation time.
    See SKILL.md § Superpowers integration → Thin SPEC format. -#}
## Implementation Approach

{{ implementation_approach | default("High-level plan that seeds the implementation plan (via swain-do). Structure as TDD cycles: identify which acceptance criteria map to which test-then-implement pairs.") }}

## Lifecycle

| Phase | Date | Commit | Notes |
|-------|------|--------|-------|
| {{ status | default("Draft") }} | {{ created_date }} | {{ commit_hash }} | Initial creation |
